et - that's in the next street here - the same number and we stayed there four years but there wasn't sufficient room - it was two bedroomed house - dad hadn't realized that - until he was there ohdear, he says, it's only got two bedrooms. I've got three 
b
oys and two girls what's going to happen so they went to the estate office which was then under Queens Park Hall at the corner of First Avenue and the gentleman at the - the clerk - they had to fill in and so on - and I think the rent was seven and six a 
w
eek - now then lady I've got the rent book - that one and I've got the other rent book of this house which was eight and six a week and - er - he took the rent book down so Mr Whitlock said well, you'll have to wait Mr Morris he said but when there is a t
h
ree bedroomed house you shall have it. So that came on then four years after and we came here - I suppose I'd be about ten then - a little more than ten and - er - I'd be the youngest one - my brother George - he was a few years older than I and then my s
ister and the two elder boys. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 What year was it you moved into this house?
