\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Why did the family move from Hanwell?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Well, because my eldest brother - and afterwar
ds my second brother were - um - at Desmond Park school which was outside Desmond Park Station - it was a - more or less Secondary school really - my eldest brother was there and then my younger - second brother Frank - that was Alfred - er - Frank was my
 
second brother - and he by accident - getting out of the train at - I believe as Desmond Park or else at Hanwell - er - caught a lady's hand in the door - he had an accident - so my father said oh well, we'll - we'll look for a house on that little estate
 that they've built at Queens Park he said then the boys won't have to go by train they can come up - they can walk up to school. So that was what happened until of course - well they left there, I suppose they were - well I don't know how old.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 How many brothers and sister did you have?
