ilver watch that was presented to dad - and I was there - in there - mother and I went with him - to - er - Ruislip - where they were - where these silver watches were presented because dad was not quite the beginning of the - of the - opening of the Met.
 
It was - I couldn't tell you how many years but - within a few years - but I know that he was one of - er - what was called the City Fathers - there were six of them - I've heard him say that there were six of them known at the City Fathers and - er - one
 in particular was a man that used to come here quite a lot - a Mr Ted Street and - er - I think he came here practically until he died really and - er - no, dad died in - dad died as I said in twenty-one - 1921 and he was then seventy-nine.
