 because as I say he was on the Met. So that when the - when he finished with the Metropolitan Railway he was home here and the only little job that he did were - was his books - grocers books - from Langleys in B
aker Street - in Belsize - er - not Baker Street - in - er - Langlays in Belsize Road - there were two brothers and there was one shop in Belsize Road and one in - I believe is still in Clifton Road. Er Percy Langley - I believe that shop is still there. 
I've been going to - when we've been up at - er - near my house I've been going to have a poke me nose round and have a look see, see if it's still there. And he used to do the grocer - grocer books up. Right until he died.
