\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Do you remember how old you would be when you started putting yourself to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 No, I can't say that I would really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Did you share the bed with your sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 With my sister - yes. With my - we two girls had the middle room - mother and dad had the ante room - w
e two girls had the middle room and the three boys two in one bed there and the elder one in a bed here - and I'll tell you another thing. er - you might laugh at this - but when this house is pulled down - if I'm not very much mistaken - when this house 
- it comes to the time this house is pulled down - under the floor - d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13249535\charrsid14891508 own - somewhere down in this wa}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 
ll is a golden sovereign - my brother Alfred hadn't been very long at work and he got this golden sovereign in his wages in he put it in his waistcoat pocke
t and put his waistcoat on the chair and when he got up I suppose picked his waistcoat up and this golden sovereign rolled out somewhere - it was never found - it was always reckoned that it went - because there was a big hole in the skirting - always rec
koned it went down there - between the wall and the skirting - er - and the flooring.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 What did you do about baths in those days -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Oh we had a big bath. Mm. Big - big - er - the big hip bath we used in the scullery. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 And how often did you have to do this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 
Well, always once a week - always Saturday night - everyone had a bath on Saturday night - one after the other and we had the copper you see alight we got plenty of hot water - oh yes, we were always clean.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Did you have clean clothes after the bath?
