\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Were you allowed to get dirty when you played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Oh well, I don't know. I suppose you got dirty - you got told off very likely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 It wasn't so easy to wash things in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 No, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Were you free to play with anyone you pleased?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Er - oh.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Did your parents discourage from playing with certain children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 W
ell, they were - we - well, I don't know that we ever bothered to play with any other children than we just associated with. Just immediately near - oh yes, I think so mostly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 There was no distinction made between children as far as you can remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 
Well, nothing - no - we were all much of a - much of a crowd really you see this street at one time was mainly - what it was built for in the first place - or what the estate was built for. When Earl Shaftesbury suggested the building of Queens Park 
Estate it was to be mainly for postmen, policeman, railway servants and - er - well, - er - social type of people - they were not - it wasn't considered to be a rough quarter - he wanted - it was to be for people who just brought up - they were family hou
s
es - from one end to the other on the whole of the estate - the family houses and as family houses they were kept. It was Lord Shaftesbury who started the - Queens Park estate in the first place. Of course - yes, and when you come to think - to consider t
hat these old trees were the original trees that were built here you know with one or two exceptions - where ........
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 In 1882 they were built?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Er - 81 - er - yes 81 - this house and this street I think was about 81 all through but - er - the begi
nning of the estate in first and second Avenue and in Caird Street where they've just began to - well, they've just pulled all down - you saw that at the bottom - where they pulled all down there and - um - a little bit I think in Third Avenue and into Dr
oop Street they were beginning to build round that part in the late - er - 1870's - right in the late 1870's until they got to this bit and they - the house where - '81.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Did anyone outside the home help your mother look after her house or family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 
Er - well, yes, well sometimes mother had an old lady - was - old up to that point - that used to come in and help her do her washing. Oh yes, because there was so much washing - there was seven of us and - er - you know, an old lady - a Mrs Woodley - use
d to come and help her - do the washing - oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 She came fairly regularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 
Er - she used to come by - once a week probably. I think she used to get about as far as the end of the - er - of the coloureds and that that - er - I think it got to s
heets and pillow cases and the copper - copper full of washing I think that was got down to about mother's time. Used - to come round and help - help mother do the wash - well - er - take the things out of the copper and rinse them up and all the rest of 
it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Did you go fishing, walks, cycling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Er - no. Not - er - not a great deal - no. Er - Nellie - my sister - had a bike but I didn't.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Did you go for walks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Oh we used to go for walks. Oh yes, we used to - one walk that we used to have
 was up over Kendal Rise station to Wellsford - was one - it was a good distance}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3690258\charrsid14891508  and - er - when we were quite}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 
 youngsters we had chickens in the back and mother used to walk over to the - a little farm place and I believe the old pub is still there where t
his little row of cottages were - I believe the old pub - I'm - not so many years ago - not long back rather - er - someone told me that they thought the old pub was still there but of course it's built all round - er - where we used to go through the but
tercup fields over Kensal Rise station there was - er - a path - a wide path and a pond and then on the right}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16482240\charrsid14891508 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 
hand side the buttercups fields and where my nephew lives now was the field where the cows were - that - er - that Wellfords had their dairy - thei
r farm - er - for the - er - dairy that provided our milk. 'Cos there was a farm over there. Yes. That was up by - er - actually - er - I don't know what it comes as now - I have heard Stanley call it - call it by name - but I know that the farm is at the
 bottom of - well, what remains of it is at the bottom of their road - the bottom of Herbert Garden.
