\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Er - oh no, about a quarter of an hour. And - um - and you were in the country part then an
d - in Kilburn Lane where Higgins Dairy stands now - er - the - the cowsheds - er - or what were the cowsheds where the - what housed the cows in those days - er - I believe still stand but you know as sheds - I don't know what they use them for now but I
 
- on the opposite side where now stands the Odeon theatre on the one corner - on the corner and then I think it's a bottling factory a bit this side of it there used to be a bridge that went right across the railway out into Harvest Road - what was then g
oing to be Harvest Road and - er - the cows when we were - er - quite }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16482240\charrsid14891508 k}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 
iddies - the cows used to come across the field and - er - put their heads over the - over the little railway bridge - over the little bridge as you went across - and they were the cows 
that were housed in Higgins - er - sheds - the man - the man would bring them out from the field and just take them round down past the shops and that shop was there then so that must be very old - really - Higgins Dairy and it's still a dairy shop too. I
t
's opposite where I go for my pension. It's still there. Yes, that shop must have been built - one of these days I'm going into the shop and ask - when I think of it - er - oh yes, I don't go up for my pension myself very often - which I haven't been up f
o
r a good long time now - er - um - my home help, Gladys, always gets it for me but I have had more than one thought of asking them what year Higgins Dairy was opened. How many years that shops been standing because I know that when we used to go - I told 
