all that was round there and that's where they used to hold their meetings at the first start off and that was really started right from St Judes Church boys - er - and these two brother Wallington were the - er - I believe were the actual starters of it 
-
 if they were not the actual starters they were there at the time that Queens Park Rangers was - was started because Frank was in it - I know Frank was in it. Oh yes, it is - oh yes, it belongs - it did belong to Queens Park estate right and proper. Oh ye
s, they were quite - they were estate boys - oh yes - they were right in the neighbourhood in those days. But when you tell people that they - they -
