\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 They don't believe you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Oh no, they - they look at you and wonder where your - er - coming or g
oing - you see. It's quite all right I know all about it. And then - er - after the Rangers Frank joined up with the Queens Park Harriers and he did it really unbeknown to my dad and he used to race a good deal in Paddington recreation ground with the har
riers and dad got to know it - dad would be at - on the - on the railway at the time because it was one of his booking clerks that saw him and he couldn't make out why Frank was going so thin - before he was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16328850 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508  this one - why he was getting so thin and
 he - he was all right - in good health and that - but he seemed very thin - dad didn't like the look of it quite and he'd spoken to the doctor about it and he said all right well he said bring him up - send him up to me I'll see what's the matter with hi
m
 and of course he was a young man out at work - he wasn't a kid at school - oh no - he was a young man out at work and - er - at all events this man happened to be standing round in the circle - and he saw Frank going to these - er - running - on more tha
n
 once occasion running with the harriers and he said to dad something about it - did you know Frank was - er - oh Frank did well in the harriers or something. Dad said I didn't know he belonged to the harriers. Oh well, he said, you go up one Saturday or 
c
ertain time - see you'll fine - you'll see him up there. And of course when dad went up and Frank caught sight of his father - he didn't run and he never ran for the harriers after that. It was - it was - er - it really was not doing him any good - he was
 
getting too thin, you see, was a case of getting thin and agile oh yes, all right, but when you were getting too thin and - er - it wasn't doing you any good - he thought it was time to stop and he - of course his excuse was that he liked to run with the 
o
thers and all the rest of it but right until the day Frank died he kept up with the harriers. He used to watch them, ooh - I was going to say he would do now if he was alive, I dare say. Right until he died. That when he died they sent him a most beautifu
l
 wreath to his home - you know - they were living in Mount Street and - er - they said for an old friend because he kept up with them and used to go there and watch the men play - sons of the men that he used to know and that - they'd all meet together th
ere. 'Course he was - he was quite a - he was - he was the only racing one in the family and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Did you go to any theatres, concerts, music-halls, cinemas while you were still at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 No. No. No. No, we never went into anything that was - I don't think I ever went into a theatre 'til I was about twenty or more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Did your parents give you any pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Oh well, yes. You couldn't get on with - you couldn't get on very far without. I - I don't know what I had - I couldn't tell you
 now. I couldn't tell you - but I know what I earned - that when I started work about the first or at least the second job that I had was in waistcoat making and I had four shillings a week. And out of that I'd got railway fare - at least, I got out of th
at, but dad had to pay my railway fare - had to go to Baker Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 When you were at school do you remember any pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Oh, I expect so. It's quite likely that I had to have pocket money to get me to go to school because I - er - being - er
 - delicate and having to take cod liver oil - and not cod liver oil and malt either - it was cod liver oil plain and simple with - er - orange juice top and bottom of it - as I went to school and then another dose at dinner time and another dose in the e
vening well - I think I wanted something sweet to - to - push it down a bit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 
If your mother was ill or confined to bed how did she manage? Do you remember what happened - you didn't have any younger brothers and sisters so you wouldn't.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 No, I di
dn't have any younger brothers and sisters. No, I expect if mother was ill my - well between the - between the family I don't know that mother was until practically the last. And then of course it came to Nellie and myself to look after her. And she was p
retty good in - er - what tummy trouble she did have really was more or less the old fashioned type of indigestion you'd call it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Did your parents have any relatives living nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Er - well, not immediately near. No. Not immediately near. No, I think most of our relations were - were country people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 How much did you see of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 
The country people? Oh well, they used to make this their home if they wanted to come to London and - anybody come to London - go to aunties - oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 You'd see them a few times a year would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Oh yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Did you go and visit them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Yes. Oh yes, we would go and visit them. Especially mother's relations - I don't know that we did dad's so much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Did your parents have friends that you would visit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Well, yes, plenty of friends coming in and out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 They'd come here to visit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Oh yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 And did they share the same friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Oh well, yes. I don't know that mother did so much - er - had - mother had one par
ticular lady friend who lived in the next street. Yes, Mrs Smith was an old lady that lived just in the next street here and - until she died - I don't know which died first - she or mother - I couldn't tell you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Where did they used to meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Oh 
she would come over - she would come round - come round the houses but - er - when I wanted to go over to Mrs Smiths to play with her daughter I used to go over the wall - yes - go over the wall.
