that any of his Forresters friends came much to the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 But were friends ever invited to the house formally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Well, I suppose so really - mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Any special occasions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Oh yes, oh any special occasion - oh yes, yes. Then you were well away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Would you say that the friends invited in were usually your mothers friends or your fathers friends?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Oh both - both - both together - yes. There was no secrets in our family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 And friends came in casually without an invitation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Oh yes, without invitation very often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Neighbours though - you tell me that neighbours ......
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 
Not so much the neighbours - no. Oh no we weren't - er - we weren't interested with - er - with neighbours popping along - er - that - er - what neighbours we did have were very good and very friendly in our older days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Did your parents ever go out to visit friends or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Well, I don't know about neighbours - but friends - I don't know that we had all that number of friends - er - outside.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 People often tell us that in those days people made their won amusements.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 We made our own amusements.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 What do you think your parents did when they got together with their friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Dad might play a game of cards - oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Did they make music?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Er - they might have done - yes, they might - he might take his concertina - I told you he'd got a concertina - he might take that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 When they came here did he play the harmonium?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 He would play - oh yes, he would play the harmonium and he would play his concertina - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 While your father and his friends were playing cards what would your mother do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Oh - she'd be inside darning the socks I expect - more than likely. Or doing a bit of ironing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Many people divi
de society into different social classes or groups - in that time before 1918 did you think of some people belonging to one class and some to another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Well, yes. Not very much really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 What were the different ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Er - there was - well the
 people that had the money didn't want to know those that hadn't got it. Very often. Yes - I had - er - many instances of that - of folks that belonged to the church. They were just a little clique together and they knew each other and they were - er - we
ll very friendly but if you don't - just weren't in that party - er - you used to stay outside the door. Still that didn't bother me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 What sort of classes in the country do you think there were in general?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Well, people that had a bit more money t
han other people didn't what to know the - those who was - who were a little less fortunate. Or - or if - or in other words who didn't want to spend their money that way, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Which sort of group would you say you belonged to yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Well,
 you wouldn't call us exactly middle class - we were - we would be the upper working class - and upper working class - oh yes, definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 There would be the working class?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 There would be the working class then the lower - then the lower paid working class - oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 And the upper working class and then there would be the middle class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 
The middle class. Yes - er - as I say the middle class people as they would call themselves would be a little bit - er - just a bit above you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 And what would you call the ones above them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Above them, I don't know. Never thought about them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 What sort of people belonged to the same class as yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Well, people whose parents would be working in much about the same - er - yes. All sor
ts of things - business people or carpenters or - er - working - working class people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Can you remember being brought up to treat people of one sort differently from another? Like were you ever told to curtsy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Show respect in some way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Well, no, I don't know that we came up against anyone that - that we would need to do -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Was there anyone you called Sir or Master or Madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Well, not until you were cut to work - then you had to call them Sir - it was Sir then all right
 - the boss. Or maybe - if - if - if you were in dressmaking - oh yes, we had - we had Madam all right - when I was in dressmaking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Do you remember anyone showing respect of this kind to your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Well, I don't know as I do, actually, not ......
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Who were considered the most important people in this district?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 
Well, mostly the people that went to church. And they were people who, in those days, if you went to church well then you were regarded as someone of - er - certain amount of importance - because ......
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 You mean church rather than chapel do you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 
Well, church or chapel - oh no, no, no - to chapel. To - er - to people who really looked to the serious side of life went to church or chapel or Salvation Army or for - churc
h army we had church army neighbours next door - who I knew for some time and - er - you would consider then that they were people that you would - er - deal with and have a good deal of conversation in common with really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 What about the shopkeepers - who did they associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Our shopkeepers - well, I couldn't tell you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 And clergy and teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 
Um - well, er - well our - our church Ministers - Ministers that we had of course at the Congregational - er - well, they were always very 
nice to everybody - oh yes, yes. But you'd be the - the people with the money or the people who hadn't got so much money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 And teachers - did they - who did they associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Who do you mean? School teachers? Well, I only know of one school te
acher that I had a great deal of - er - feeling and liking for - she was a Miss Everton - when I was in Droop Street school and I was very fond of her and she was very fond of my mother and she used - she lived Empress Avenue with her mother until she was
 }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16328850 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508  - well at least after she was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16328850 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508  for that matter, see 'til her mother died - and - er - she used to come round here on her way home - walk home with - oh two or three of us hanging on her arm and come in and have a cup of tea - mother knew jus
t what time we would be home and there'd be a cup of tea and a piece of cake - home made cake - and this with Miss Emerson - and afterwards she became a Mrs Harris and - er - oh yes, and she was very friendly - not only with me but with the girls - oh yes
, no - there was no favour}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16482240\charrsid14891508 itism. Oh no, there was no favou}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 ritism.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 And no class distinction?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Oh no, no. No class distinction at all - but she was ......
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Did you ever notice anything about farmers - who they associated with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Farmers? No, I never had much to do with farmers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 And employers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Well, they would only be the - in what way employers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 People who employed you for instance - who would they mix with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Well, all depends on which job it was - that does really, in a
 way, yes. Well, now - er - yes - I'm afraid I changed my jobs so many times one way and another - er -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Was there any social difference between the people who went to church and the people who went to chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Er - not a great deal - no. Er - the
re was at first - when we first came here - there was a certain distinction between the Church of England. Er - that was I think due to the - er - Vicar of St Judes. St Judes was a very low church and the Vicar there I think thought that everyone ought to
 
go to his church. Well, when the Congregational Minister came to Queens Park my - 'course I was born - I was sort of bred and born in Church of England - I was christened in - er - Church of England and my father and mother used to go to Church of England
 
before we came to London you see. But when we came to London the - er - mother didn't care about St Judes and she didn't care about listening to the - the old Vicar and it finished up that my sister was going there to Sunday school and I suppose I was too
 
but it was Nellie that the query was with and she got a little girl friend that went to school with her - that she went to school with - er - and this child had not been christened. And Nellie wanted her to go to Sunday school with her to St Judes and - o
h
 no, said Mr - Mr Sidney Bott - oh no, he couldn't have her in the Sunday school because she hadn't been christened. So Nellie came home weeping that - er - whatever the girls name was couldn't go to Sunday school with her because they'd been to - er - an
d
 had been into the church - er - church - er - Congregational and that but - er - she couldn't go - she couldn't go to Church of England to St Judes because she hadn't been christened. So my dad said oh, like that is it, well, common come with me. So with
 
these two girls and himself he goes round to see Mr Sidney Bott. See, we've come to live in this district and my daughter wants to go to your Sunday school. Oh very good, yes, very good, quite good, yes, but you didn't ask me one question. What's that? Ha
d
 she been christened. And he looked. Dad said - because this other little girl - you have told - er - them - that that child cannot come to your Sunday school because she hasn't been christened. Oh no, no, he said, I couldn't have any children that haven'
t
 - my children must all be christened before they join our Sunday school. Dad said, very good then, thank you, Mr Bott in future he said, my daughter will go with her little friend and they'll join - join in the Sunday school at Queens Park Congregational
 
Church. From henceforth on. And they did. And Nell - Alfred was the only one that used to ever go to St Judes. The eldest - my eldest brother. No, Nellie hung on and my sister Nell - when that church was built - her son found this out a little while ago -
 
a few years back - Nellie collected the most money to buy the most bricks of any child in the Sunday school and - er - when Stanley saw it - Eliza Ellen Morris - why he said that's my mum. Oh good lor'. And then they were - were looking through some of th
e
 records belonging to the church - he said that was my old mum, I must tell her that when I got home and so he came in straight away and told her. And she said yes, I know I did, she said, I collected the most money and I don't know what she got in return
 for it - I couldn't tell you.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Was there any friction between the church and the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 
Er - I don't know there was any friction but I - don't know that there was a great deal of love lost - not with that particular man. Because he was - um - a
lthough he was very low church - but he was not - um - er - he wasn't - I don't say prejudiced - but he just - er - I don't think he ever associated with Queens Park. And the other church - St Johns up at Kensal Green - corner of Kilburn Lane and harrow R
o
ad - that was a higher church altogether and the further on it went the higher up it went. That is very high church. As far as I know - I haven't been in it for a good many years but - r - it is - but - er - there was that - I don't say that there was any
 
prejudice but they just didn't - er - if you went to one you went to one you stuck to it you see. And then of course we had a Baptist church at the top of Gilbert Street, well then that we did associate with and - er - well the place it is now - er - ware
h
ouse - used to be a primitive Methodist church - one of the old fashioned Primitive Methodists - what they called the Bible thumpers - er - sometimes the children used to go round there - used to all go round there - er - to Lantern Services. They would h
a
ve a lantern service in the church or else in the class room down below for the children and that but we used to go round there you see. But - er - then we had another little church that - well what we call Hoepoors - just this last few years been rebuilt
 
and - and to this day I couldn't tell you what the actual religion of it is - no. We never could seem to fathom quite what it is - er - their certainly not Jehovah Witnesses - oh no, long way off that. Er - but whether - and they're not Methodist - they m
ight be of the old fashioned Plymouth Brethren but - er - oh I have been to this - er - just - er - well, a little sort of hope Hall and it was just an ordinary little Sunday turn.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Did all the people in the working class have the same standard of living - or would you say there were differences?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 
The seem - no, just the - I should say - well, as I said, er - those of us that considered ourselves - well - I don't say above everybody else but - er - you were all of a like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 What about the lower working class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Oh we only had a few - very, very few. I think - they - they - well they would be a bit lower - oh yes, but I don't think we had many.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 I remember you told me about a little girl who didn't have any shoes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Oh yes, they, were -
 oh that was not in this neighbourhood - that was over the bridge - oh yes. Oh yes, well that was a lower class neighbourhood altogether. Er - well I suppose it's altered a good deal now but where they housed these people I couldn't tell you. Er - over in
 Kensal Road - over in that part really belongs to Kensington - over the ha'penny - what we call the ha'penny bridge. Belongs to Kensington.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Do you think that one group felt itself superior to the rest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Er - well yes, yes, up to a point, yes. And
 then we had another seat - or section of people that were down the Harrow Road - over what we called Loch bridge - it was just past Paddington Hospital - you know where Paddington Hospital is - just on the brew of that hill - you that - on ei}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16482240\charrsid14891508 ther side now a tall block of f}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16482240\charrsid14891508 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 
ts aren't there. Well, immediately you got over the - that you got over the bridge the slope of the bridge you had a very low quarter on that side - Brindly Street - you had - er - Clarendon Street - Winchester Street - Celia Street - o
h and I couldn't tell you the names of the others that were at the back - I never went down any of those back turnings - but those turnings - until you got right to the level of what is now Royal Oak Station - out in the Harrow Road - you wouldn't know it
 
- that being - it being - er - told to you, but all down to that part were the lower class all together - very lower class - working class. They would be on the same level as the other people over in Kensal Road - yes - very much lower class of people - a
lthough - er - now and again you would meet people that were quite nice but they lived under very hunched up conditions. Oh yes, in many, many cases.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Do you remember a distinction of this kind between craftsmen and labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Oh yes, oh yes. The
re would be a distinction. Yes, a craftsman was a craftsman and he - he let you know it but - er - a labourer would be a man who - well, say a dustman as it was then - the old dustman that would - er - come with the van - the dustcart and his gee-gee and 
h
e'd go up the steps and he'd empty your dustbin - no, it wouldn't be your dustbin - it would be a basket - they would come through the house and where my coal cellar is now used to be - er - was a brick built coal cellar - er - dustbin and they would lift
 it up and take the dust through. But they were considered - they were lower paid - very much lower paid. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12342286\charrsid14891508 Now}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 
 the people that I lived with - er - in Bravington Road before I came to live with Nellie. Er - Mr Bonnington's father was a dustman and he used to 
say how nice it was to come round some of the streets and get a bit of social - people would be sociable with you - even though you were the dustman you see - oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 They lived differently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 They did - their life was quite different - oh yes. Er - in fact - going over the bridge - when - er - I told you about the children}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12342286\charrsid14891508 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 
s outings and - and - er - parties that we had - well, in many, many cases we were not allowed - although we were grown up women - we were not allowed - when I say not allowed i
t wasn't considered right for you to go into some of those lower class places with your tickets for the children}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12342286\charrsid14891508 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 
s parties - but our business - belonging to the church would take them - because the chances were if you were a stranger unless you'd got a Sal
vation Army bonnet on you might get something thrown out the top floor window instead of them emptying down the lavatory they'd throw it out the window.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 And did this actually - this sort of thing happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Well, well, oh I know - so the story goes
 - I - and I think it was true - oh yes, I believe it was true at times if you were a complete stranger or if you looked a bit different - er - you looked a bit better off than what they did. Oh yes I believe that was the case really - both over there and
 
over in Kensal Road. Yes. They were very, very rough some of the people, mm, I don't say they weren't honest they might have been honest - oh yes - I wouldn't take a persons character away - they might have been honest but they - know and considered thems
elves in a - a far lower grade than what you did. Because when you finished up with these children}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12342286\charrsid14891508 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 
s tea and outings and all the rest of it - er - well, during the war - in the first war - you found that many of those children's parents - the father and brothers would be away in the war - mother hadn't got them to keep - mother would be working on \{
ILLEGIBLE\} - good luck to her - and all the daughters would be working on something that they could earn a good wage at where the majority of us - or many of us -
 er - were people who didn't earn a big wage - I know I was only earning about sixteen or seventeen shillings a week as a dressmaking for Derry and Thoms during that time - during 1914 to 1917 - no, no no - 19 - no wait a minute - 1912 to 1915, I was earn
ing about sixteen to seventeen shillings a week as a dressmaker - I was not - our first hand only had a pound a week. And so then we decided then that these munition people were earning more and didn't need the amount of help - so we packed up children}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12342286\charrsid14891508 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 s teas and dinners and parties.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Did your mother and father have the same attitude to people belonging to different classes or group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Oh yes, oh yes, yes. Yes they were all - everything was just - just homely and ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Do you think your mother saw herself as belonging to a particular social class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 
Not all that much - no. Oh no. She was quite - I don't say that she made a great deal of fuse with many of they people in the immediate neighbourhood, but - er - she was very much liked. Very, very much liked - until - right until she died.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Was it possible in those days to move from one class to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Well, if you were getting up in the world a bit then of course you did. And you moved away then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Can you remember anyone who did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 
Oh yes, we had several people in this street - yes. Several of our folks who got a better job - moved away - oh yes. Didn't come back anywhere near to see you. Oh - went up in the world - oh yes, many people really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Do you remember anyone being described as a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 
Well, no - well - not in the average people - no. Now there was one lady that I did associate with who was very kind on Paddington - she was on Paddington Borough council and she lived at Paddington - some
where by Paddington station. She was a lady of quality - she was a Miss Katherine Bruce and if I'm not out of the question I think that the nursery at the top of Albert Street is named after her - I believe that children's nursery is name after her - as M
i
ss Matherine Bruce - I believe that's what it's called. It's either Katherine or it's Katherine Bruce Center. Er - and she was very kind - er - and always sent me a pound for our childrens outing right until our children - until we packed up doing our chi
ldren}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12342286\charrsid14891508 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 s outing - and she was quite a lady - oh she was a sweet person very, very nice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Do you remember seeing a policeman round where you lived?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Policeman? Policeman? Yes, they always come round here. It's only just of late years that we haven't had our policeman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 What did you think of him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 He was - they're a novelty when you see one now. Say what do you come for - do you want me?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 What did you thing of him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Well, I, I .....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 When you were naughty did your mother ever say I'll call a policeman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 
Oh, I don't know that she ever did that but - er - well you always - you know - the boys and the girls - I must say that - as far as I remember - as youngsters - er - you had a certain amount of respect for the policeman. You k
now what the policeman's duties were and I'm not going to say as - as life went on - whether - whether the boys got a ball that they shouldn't be playing with - that they didn't just lose that ball somewhere or other in the meantime if they saw a policema
n coming but that wasn't right - er - in my very much younger days - oh no. We used to play with our ball and if by chance a child had an accident and the ball went through somebody's window well father paid for it. It was put in and father paid for it.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 How do you think he treated people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 
Our policeman. Well I think that they - well I don't know that I think I - he looked - looked upon it as his duty to look after the welfare of the neighbours - of the people. If there was any trouble well - a pol
iceman was always - would always be on the spot - he wasn't far away. We had a bit of trouble here while I was away. Family up this street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Was your home rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Yes, this one - oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Did you see anything of your landlord?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Er 
- well it wasn't rented from a .. ours was not rented from a landlord it was rented from a company - it was the artisans company you see and your - er - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12342286\charrsid14891508 r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 ent man came from the rent office wherever it was - mostly in the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12342286\charrsid14891508 N}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 arrow Road and ....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 What were they like as landlords?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 
Oh, as the company? Well - er - the artisans company you see you paid for your - in your rent - you paid for all normal repairs if you wanted anything done - if you wanted a fireplace set in - a new fireplace set in or there's
 a chimney broken you fill up a form and that went up to the estate office because there was an office that I believe still there - at the top of - er - Albert Street - er - and they would take note of it - er - chimney stack - er - or chimney out of orde
r
 or chimney broken or gutters - guttering is bad and you would - er - the workmen would come down within a day or two and repair it - the same as they do now. That goes - that stands just as now. Oh yes - oh they're quite good - er - as the artisans but o
f
 course it belongs to Westminster now but - oh yes, yes all belongs to the council - but I suppose the Westminster - er - the artisans and general dwellings as they used to be called - er - I suppose they're all bought up I couldn't tell you. I couldn't t
ell you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Do you remember feeling that your parents had to struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 No. I don't think they ever did really. Not in my lifetime. I don't know what happened before I was born.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 And your father was never out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Oh, no, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Nor did he have to get help from the Parish?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Oh good lord no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Were you given lessons by one of your parents or a tutor or governess?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Oh no. No. But dad - dad would always help me with my sums in the evenings - if I was
 a bit stuck and - er - if I was - you know - bit - thinking of what I hadn't done then I went to bed with that on my mind - what would very often happen you'd see me sitting an hour or two afterwards on the stairs working out my sums on my fingers. Dad'd
 
say here listen - he says there's that girl on the now come along, up to bed - and I'm still talking about my sums - and up to bed - he'd settle me into bed - goodnight - give me a kiss goodnight. I'd go off to sleep - forget - the next morning he'd say n
ow what was the matter with that sum you couldn't do last night. Oh I don't know dad. But I suppose I did it. You did it sitting on the stairs. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 So he was able to help you quite a lot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Yes, he did with his - yes - but - er - when I was ill
 - er - when I was between eight and nine and I had these abscesses I think I told you about - er - I think that perhaps as I see things now - if dad had - er - if they had arranged at the school that dad put me through what they'd been doing the day befo
r
e at the - in the school - in Droop Street school - that - er - I should have picked up things that I otherwise lost so that I had to go back into the sixth standard again - when I got my sixth standard certificate it was either go to the Holborn Street s
c
hool and take a chance or - er - go back into the sixth standard again and - er it was decided that I should do better if I went through the sixth standard again because I wasn't proficient - sufficient you see to go really to go to the seventh standard s
o
 when I went to - to the Holborn Street which was our finishing school instead of going into the seventh standard then I went into the X seventh. Because I was that twelve months older and I went into the X seventh. Er - but I think if we'd have - if I'd 
have had the bit of schooling in the evening - perhaps it was thought that I wasn't well enough - because I was ill - I really was ill - oh yes - with the abssesses - that wasn't in this house - it was in the next.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Because in those days it was very serious wasn't it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 
Oh yes because - oh it hung like - great big lumps and the doctor wouldn't have them lanced from the inside - he wouldn't let me go to the hospital and have them lanced - said no he was going to cure me and they - there's this one fi
lled up - that one was - er - er - coming through - great loosely plastered round your head-horrible. Week in and week out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 How old were you when you first went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Now I don't think I went to school at Hanwell - well I must have done - o
h yes, because I was six and half when we come up here so I must have done because we would go to school in the ordinary way at five, so I expect I did twelve months at - er - Hanwell - er - Hanwell - um - church school where the others went to and then I
 
came into Droop street because I didn't go into the infants - so possibly I was in the infants there at Hanwell and then when I came up to here - up to Queens Park I went straight into the first standard. 'Cos I can always remember those were - at least I
 
was looking at them the other day - when I passed there on Wednesday - I said that was the room I was first in when I came to Droop Street school - I said to the lady that was sitting next to me. She said - you remember. I said of course I remembered - I 
said and I remember the teacher I had too - it was Miss Emerson - oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Of course these people were very important in your lives weren't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Oh yes, they were, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Can you remember what time you went to school in the morning and what time you came home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Nine o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 This was when you first started school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 
Oh yes, yes. Yes, well, when we would go to - when I would go to Droop Street and you would hear that old bell ringing and I hear it now sometimes - well, when they start - they'll be starting next week - you can hear that tell go just before nine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 And what time did you come home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Er - now we did longer hours - then - I think it was half past four. Well, nine to twelve - it would be nine 'til twelve and then 
we went back at two 'til half past four - yes, I think that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Do you remember what time it was when you were at Hanwell?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Er - no, I wouldn't remember much of that - I don't remember much of - er - of there at Hanwell - not all that amount
. Although as I told you the other day, I - I remembered the house when I saw it a few weeks back. Stanley was amazed when I told him that. I said you know Bessie took me down to - er - to St Marks Road. He said well I couldn't find that St Marks Road whe
n
 I was looking - when I was round that way the other day with the car. I said you jolly well didn't look far - I said if you turned - taken the turnings - there's May - I said if you'd taken the turnings that I told you - you'd have found out where it was
.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 You've already told me it was a church school you went to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Oh yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 This one here's a church school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 No, this is council school. This was - um - well it became council - it all went council after - oh what did we used to
 call it - a board school. Board school - yes, that's it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 And it was a day school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Day school - yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Was it mixed - boys and girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 No. No, it was the girls downstairs and boys up - oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 You were kept separate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Yes, well - er - our training - with our training we were all - um - girls down - stairs and boys up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 You didn't mix at play times?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 No, I think our playground - no, I think the girls had the back - playground at the back - now they have half of this - i
n fact I don't know what they do actually at there now. I couldn't tell you what they do because it might be a mixed school even now. Quite likely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 How long did it take you to get there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 About five minutes I dare say - running.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Who went with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 
Well, no one - no one with us no. When I was - when I - well, when I'd be six or seven - you know - I - I'd go to school on my own - and on the foggy - er - you got foggy days when you couldn't see the other side of the street and didn't know 
whether the other side of the street was a field or whether it was - or whether it was houses. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11211013\charrsid14891508 W}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 e did have some smokey fogs.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Where did you have your mid-day meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Home. I came home from school. Yes, and when I came home from school I got dosed u
p for a long time with - er - cod liver oil. When I went to school I had - I'd had me dose of cod liver oil - oh for quite a long time. Horrible stuff.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 What did you think of school - did you like it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Oh - I liked my school - I liked Droop Street
 school - yes - very much - yes. We had a little person was - that was our governess and she always used to take the French lesson as we got older - she was always took our - Miss Burton. She used to take the French - the French lesson, but I just hated t
hat old French - give me English I can get on with it but give me French and I can't get on with that. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 How did you feel about the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 The teachers were all very nice. Yes. We had ones - one was a Mrs Walker, one was a Mrs Bedford - I think they were both - would both be }
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16328850 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 
 ladies - by being a Mrs - and then there was Miss Emerson - Mrs Harris as she became. But - er - they were always very good. And it's not long ago that I was talking to someone that apparently was in the school a 
little bit younger than myself but that was in the school at the same time as I was. But she would be in the younger class coming up you see - at Droop Street - oh yes. But there are not many of the old ones left now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Did the teachers emphasise certain things as being important in life - such as manners?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 
I don't - manners? Oh well, yes, oh yes. If you didn't have behave yourself you went into the governors. You knew what the governors meant - the second time into the governors it meant the cane. 
But - er - unless you were - had done something that - er - well wasn't just - much - but .....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 And tidiness - did they emphasis tidiness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Well, I suppose so - about as - as they would naturally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 And punctuality?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Oh yes. Oh yes, yes. We used to - got to be in to school on time. Run like billy-o.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 How about ways of speaking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 
In the way of speaking? Well yes, of course, it would be - what - looked upon now as old fashioned but - er - well, we always - we were taught to behave ourselves always and to be truthful and they got the truth out of us all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 If you did something the teachers disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Oh I don't know - I expect you got the cane then. Well, you were warned quite possibly, I - I wouldn't know - that's .....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Would the girls be treated the same as the boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 
I wouldn't know - no the boys were upstairs. I apparently was there part of the time with my brother 'til - George - George would be upstairs because I was thinking yeste
rday that he didn't leave Droop Street until he was twelve - he was twelve rather when he left Droop Street - I was two years younger so I'd be ten so I had then about three years in Droop Street with him but that was when he left - I think I told you tha
t
 little bit about the - um - about him going to what was called Queens Park College - I think I told you about that. I know I've got to talk to the - I've got to talk to Mr Cummins or to the Mayor of Westminster about that little lot - when he comes - if 
I
'm lucky enough that he comes along sometime I'm hoping to see him because I want to show him that book and I don't want that book in the condition that it's in - er - to go out from the house - no. Because I must get Suey my pal that's been in the bookbi
nding trade - er - to try and do something with it for me - she did say she would some time ago but it didn't get done but that book must be attended to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Did your parents show an interest in your school work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Oh yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Did they ask what you did at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 
Oh yes, I expect so, you know, and say - most parents that had got a bit of time 'cos dad was - dad was particular about his children - er - having a good - reasonably good education otherwise he wouldn't have sent the two boys t
o the better class school because the school that the two elder boys went to - er - Alfred and Frank - er - was Westlands schools which was on the level of our - er - Grammar schools would be today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Did your parents visit the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Well, that 
I couldn't tell you. I don't know that they ever had occasion to. I couldn't say that they ever had occasion to - mother - if so it would be mother - it wouldn't be dad. Would be mother - but I don't know that she ever had occasion to. I was - except at t
h
e time when it was the change over that I should stay back to Droop Street because I'd been ill you see, she probably was asked to come and see then, oh yes, quite likely, come and see the governors because you see they wouldn't put me back into that clas
s a second time without consulting your parents - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Did they meet the teachers otherwise do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 
Er - only the one - the one - Miss - er - Miss Emerson - the one that used to come and have a cup of tea with us before she went home. She was very nice - expect she's gone long before now - I don't know what became of her in the finish.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Did the other children come from similar types of homes to your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Oh yes, yes. As far as I know - er - as far as I know we were all - nice - what 
we would call respectable - young people - I don't know that we had any of the rough or - no I don't think we did - not as far as I remember Droop Street school.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Did the teachers single out some children for different treatment from the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Er - that I don't know. No, there was never - you weren't consulted on anything really much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 You didn't notice them sort of making more of one child than another or less?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Oh no, I don't think so. No, I think we were all - oh no, no. So long as 
we all behaved ourselves and that I think we were all treated on a level - oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Were there any gangs or groups in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 No, not that I know of. No. I think we all trooped in - trooped out - er - at playtime and then we'd go back again a
nd come off at dinner time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Were some children left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 No, I don't think so. I think not. Not for any reason.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 And then you went to another school after?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Yes, went to Beethoven - one of the - now it is a training school at 
the present time - they've made a training school of it for the - er - students - students - more or less a miniature training college - well, there's more - I think it's more commercial - mm. In - er - sort of Technical - mm - er - on a small scale becau
se I don't think there's many of them there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 How old were you when you went there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Well, I'd be about thirteen I suppose - thirteen - and I did about twelve months - twelve - thirteen I suppose round about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 And what were the hours there - were they the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Oh yes. Same - oh yes, they were all the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 And what was this sort of school called?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11211013\charrsid14891508 Beeth}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 oven school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 And was it a board school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Oh yes, it was just the same - it was the same as Droop Street but there
 was just a little bit higher - the classes went up a little bit higher. You see. Er - and there - er - there were just that much in advance of Droop Street by reason of the fact that on the walls of that school until the last few years - were hung the ho
n
ours board - an honours board and they'd go right the way round the school they did - went right round the school on the walls and anybody listening to that would corroborate what I'm telling you. You - all those for that year - what they'd done and what 
t
heir qualifications were - I know one - I can remember the name of one boy - I can't pick up the others for the moment - but I remember was the nephew of one of the teachers - he was Willie Richardson and I can see that boys name in gilt letters up there 
w
hen he'd gone up from the X seventh and finished his name was on the honours board. And it's only a few years ago that those boards were taken down. When my sister and I went round there before Nellie died - it would be about the twelve months before Nell
 died 'cos I know our next door neighbour took us - Robert - er - to do our voting - I said lets go and have a look at the old school because Nellie used to work there - she worked there for twenty years you see - er -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 How did you get to Beethoven school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Oh the same as Droop Street - just round the corner - about five minutes walk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 And you went there how long?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Beethoven Street - oh I was fourteen - thirteen fourteen.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 And where did you have your mid-day meal then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 My meal - yes - always come home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 What did you think of this school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 
Well, of course it was better than Droop Street. Oh what I was going to - what I was telling you about the honours board they were there until - um - the last time as I said when my sist
er and I went round to do our voting and we went in to have a look at the old school and looked up - said to the caretaker what have you done with the honours boards? Oh, he said they scrapped them years - some years ago. I said, scrapped them what did th
e
y do - where did they put them. Oh yes said, scrapped them. I said - ooh I think some of those young men and the girls that must be getting older that were at Beethoven at that time - I expect - er - to know they'd gone up in flames I'd expect there'd hav
e
 been some trouble about it. Yes, they should have kept them - the school was there and those honour boards should never have been scrapped. What on earth - of course it's used as a training school but that doesn't matter - let them be up there - because 
- er - I think Beethoven Street was opened before Droop Street - I'm not sure but I think that was the - I thought I could hear the old school bell going - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 How did you feel about the teachers there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Oh our teachers were quite good - we had all men teachers. They were all men teachers there - during that twelve months.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Was this mixed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 
Er - yes. Yes, it was - we were mixed - yes, boys and girls to each - er - seat. Oh yes, yes. We had the boys with us. I don't know anything special about them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 How did you feel about the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Oh our teachers were all right. I think they only actually - there goes my postman - how letters have you brought me this time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Did the teachers at Beethoven Street emphasise things that were important in life like manners, tidiness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 
Well, well, yes I think they would because you see you were all just that bit older - leaving school - and I think you then had things drilled into you - er - yes, - er - punctuality and what you looked forwar
d to when you started out to work because you see you would start at - in our time you would start work practically as soon as you - as soon as you finished school - at that - er - summer session - you would finish and you would get into a job or - if you
 
went into work straight away, but I think I didn't - I think - I'm almost sure that the first year - if not the two - first winters - that I was at home with mother. You know, helping mother and that - because they didn't bother with me - er - getting a j
ob immediately because I know I must have been about sixteen - um - when I got a - when I was put into a job which was waistcoat making - off Baker Street - which - for which I got the noble sum of four bob a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 If you did something the teachers disapproved of there what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 
Oh I think you went up to the headmaster then. Er - and got just told off - er I forget who our headmaster was at that time because I think old Mr Tait had left couldn't tell you who the headmaster was then - but 
at any rate I remember there was a gallery which I believe is still there, where he would be and the school choir, the violins and so on up there in the morning - for the morning session - and - er - anything happened in the meantime - during the morning 
y
ou had to go upstairs or you thought that was tragic - but I never had to go upstairs. I never went up to the headmasters room at all. And - er - had no occasion for the length of time I was there - you see I would only be there a little over the twelve m
onths.
