and then I was finished. Er because I know that I - I know that - um - I think I went to stay with my cousin at Hampstead for about a month when she was - er - parlourmaid to Frederick Hill I told you - that's Roland Hill's brother - er - and I think I we
n
t to stay with either with my cousin Tilly as we called her or else it was that Tilly had gone home - er - for this month and I stayed with the cook. I don't know which it was for the minute. Because I know it was - that was really the fact of me leaving 
s
chool because - er - a bit before the actual school holiday - because they knew that I would be finishing within a week or two you see and it was - er it was satisfactory then that I should finish to go and be with this person. I don't know which one it w
as - whether it was Tilly or - er - Jenny the cook that was - um - away for - er - for someone being ill. I don't know - that was me - the finish but - it was quite happy there - oh yes.
