did when she first - er - used to go to school - when she - you know - came from here - she - she - er - used to go to evening classes. Er - I think it was cooking - wouldn't be dressmaking - er - cooking I think - cookery classes, yes of course it was - 
i
t was the cookery class that was over at what is Mobile school now - secondary school and I believe that that kitchen is still there. If you looked in the front gates I think to the left - to the right rather - um - to the left is the school and to the ri
ght would be the - what used to be the cookery school. Oh yes, I remember going there for cookery - for cookery lessons - and
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 In the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Oh no - during the school day and - yes - that would be either from Droop Street or Beethoven I don't kn
ow which at the moment and I know that we used to go for laundry work where you had to take collars - you had to take a collar to wash and then you were taught to - um - shine it, you know, glaze it - I've forgotten what you had to do with it, but I know 
i
t's not very long ago - er - oh well, in the first place I wanted - er - a round - what was called a round iron - a - a - round iron - a smooth - a smoothing - an iron that would be used for the - for the opening of seams underneath in velvet - in old - i
n
 the older days - as I got older and I remember buying that iron - a woman bought it for me rather - outside a pawnshop I think for about sixpence and it's not long ago - not above two years ago that I took that glazing iron over to my niece at Walthamsto
w
 for her doorstop - I told them that I'd got - they happened to speak about it and I said well when Stan's bringing me over at Christmas I said I'll bring that iron over for your door - front door-stop because their house is the front and the back well wh
e
n the dustman comes in there you've got to - er - when the dustman comes in there you've got to hold onto your back door and it's - I said look here I'll give you a door-stop because we've got this big thick piece of iron you see for ours and - er - I'll 
bring you my flat iron - er - my iron - not my flat iron but my - round iron and oh Alf was very pleased with it and he had it shone up and ......But that was my holiday. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Do you have any regrets about your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Do you think you benefited from attending school?
