\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 No, we never worked Sundays. Oh, no, no, we never had to work Sundays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Then you went to Derry and Thoms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Then from there I went to Derry and Thom
s in the skirt room. Er - making and - er - altering - because we had alterations at the same time that came up into our work room. Well I was talking about our work room. In fact that - this bit of - crochet I was showing - I was talking to May - and I s
a
id to him - can you - can you - Nell said can you crochet - he said I can manage to make a chain - because thinking about it - before you go to - don't go before I show you some balls that I've made - big balls - now I want to show them to you - er - roun
d
 - er - I said as a matter of fact may I had my bit of - one bit of crochet that I remembered I did keep - 'cos I used to do a lot of fancy work and little mats and things but this one I remember making perfectly well when I was at Derry and Thoms in our 
d
inner time that I - I crocheted that - oh no, we used to sit - we used to go upstairs from our work room into what wouldn't be allowed today - there'd be the wash bowls there and there'd be about four or five lavatories there and we'd take our sandwiches 
