\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 How long did you stay at the Post Office?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 
Four years. I was one of the first to go in - one of the last to come out - in 19 - er - 1919. 1915 to 1919. And it was just about this week - it was just about - I know I've got a birthday just - that's why I told you I was thirty-five. Er - I - er -
 I got a birthday just at that time but - er - I suppose that was why it was I was one of the older ones - I was asked to be a section leader. You see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 I forgot to ask you how you felt about Derry and Thoms as employers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Oh they - Derrys - good,
 yes, very good people. For employers. Of course I came out from there to go to the - er - the Post Office - oh yes, oh yes. We were - er - oh we were all very happy there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 The very first job when you left school - was it an actual job - you know, whe
n you went to Hampstead - before you went into waistcoat making - didn't you go and work with this relative who was a parlourmaid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5453887 HB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 Oh no, no, I didn't go - I didn't go to work there. I only went to stay with her oh no, no. Oh no, that was another matter all together.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8795008 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 What jobs have you done since the first world war?
