 the training of unemployed women. You had young - quite young people and you had women that were quite elderly. Er - this was in - well sort of doing all sorts of things - munitions and stuff during the war - and wanted to do something better in needlewo
rk - and there were three of us - there was a superintend}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166099\charrsid14891508 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 nt and we other two who were - the superintend}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10166099\charrsid14891508 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 
nt - I don't know who she was chosen by - I can't remember - but - er - we two that were the workers looking after the workers - er - were chosen by the
 - er - er - Middlesex County Council - the how and the why I can't tell you, but I know that I had to go to get the job - that was where the advertisement came in from - was the - er - Middlesex Guildhall - er - Westminster that I had to go to - where I 
a
ctually got the job. And I got - I got it in preference to another woman who thought she was going to get it because she was a scientific dressmaker - she was quite sure she was going to get the job - I think there were three of us in the swim. And the ot
her one I think was too old - er - I think she was a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16328850 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6820256\charrsid14891508 
 woman - she was - she was too old - she couldn't concentrate on the job that was wanted - I was single you see and - er - able to - er - put me mind onto the sewing to teach - show girls how to th
ey should use a machine and how they should sew this and do that but I never knew such a lot of blockheads in all my life. Oh. Talk about work. No more than hold a needle. Some - they couldn't hold a needle much less - er - didn't know which way to put th
e
 needle in I don't think - whether they put it in this way up or that way up. Er - much less do a bit of machining and they had twelve brand new Singers machines - brought for this - er - Harlesden Memorial Hall I think it was - I know it was right up in 
Harlesden going down Stonebridge - er - towards Wembley. Er - I remember this building was and we - we two had - er three pound a week - school hours - nine 'til five and no Saturdays - nine to five Monday to Friday - oh I thought I was quite in.
